comments.body: Superseded by #6175.
Can't replicate. Closing.

There were 235 charges on CDL items during this date range. the 2 items with the most charges each had 2 charges; they were:
- https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/1fc753d7-006f-4e51-bb41-55314e3dd7e9
- https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/a2ef34cb-7102-4fb0-b662-91aa4079dd59

Here's the code I used to get these numbers:
```
> query_service = ChangeSetPersister.default.query_service
> lists = query_service.find_all_of_model(model: CDL::ResourceChargeList)
> with_items = lists.select { |l| l.charged_items.present? }
> range_start = Date.parse("2023/01/09")
=> Mon, 09 Jan 2023
> range_end = Date.parse("2023/12/31")
=> Sun, 31 Dec 2023
> charges_in_range = {}
> with_items.each do |list|
*   items_in_range = list.charged_items.select { |i| i.expiration_time <= r ange_end && i.expiration_time >= range_start }
*   charges_in_range[list.resource_id] = items_in_range if items_in_range.p resent?
> end
> charges_in_range.values.flatten.count
=> 235
> counts = charges_in_range.to_a.map { |tuple| [tuple[0], tuple[1].count] }
> counts.select { |tuple| tuple[1] > 1 }
=>
[[#<Valkyrie::ID:0x00007f137a35b440 @id="1fc753d7-006f-4e51-bb41-55314e3dd7e9">, 2],
 [#<Valkyrie::ID:0x00007f135c3233b0 @id="a2ef34cb-7102-4fb0-b662-91aa4079dd59">, 2]]
```

comments.body:
[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/65278155/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/65278155)

coverage: 95.557%. remained the same
when pulling **a6c94e42701778bd663b145463414f04df4a3491 on revert-3937-fix-cas-login-for-devs**
into **40372d6889813ad3a568eae4c8ccc59e7e012077 on main**.

Looking at the stacktrace the user selected two volumes (E) and (A). A is already out on loan via Borrow Direct. The error came up because the code asked for a contact email from this location https://bibdata.princeton.edu/locations/holding_locations/RES_SHARE$IN_RS_REQ which has no delivery locations attached. I'm not 100 sure why the code is calling this a for an item that is a resource sharing request. Need to research if that is really necessary since the request system does not send staff notifications for ILLiad requests. However I think if we give this location a delivery location with an email we won't see these errors any longer.
